dataset.description:
3-4-50 Chronic Disease data from the year 2000. 3-4-50 represents the three behaviors (poor diet, physical inactivity, and tobacco use) which contribute to four chronic diseases (cancer, heart disease and stroke, type 2 diabetes, and pulmonary diseases such as asthma) that cause over 50 percent of all deaths worldwide.

 *Rates per 100,000 population. 
Deaths with unknown Region or SRA are reflected in the county total, but not in the individual categories. Category sums may not add up to county total.							3-4-50 Deaths include Stroke, Coronary Heart Disease (CHD), Diabetes, COPD, Asthma, and Cancer.
§ Rates and Percentages not calculated for fewer than 5 events.  Rates not calculated in cases where zip code is unknown.										
Source: Death Statistical Master Files (CA DPH), County of San Diego, Health & Human Services Agency, Epidemiology & Immunization Services Branch; SANDAG, Current Population Estimates, 10/2000-10/2013.
Prepared by County of San Diego (CoSD), Health & Human Services Agency (HHSA), Community Health Statistics, 2015.
dataset.title: 3-4-50 Chronic Disease Deaths 2000-2013

dataset.description:
This atlas shows the location of selected food retailers in San Diego County. Retailer data were obtained from the California Department of Health, California Nutrition Network, which classified them according to the type of establishment (grocery, fast food, etc.). In addition, the maps show the locations of certified farm markets, farm stands, community-supported agriculture farms (CSAs) and community gardens. Not
all retail food vendors are shown (caterers, spice/herb suppliers, and vitamin/nutrition stores were not mapped). Retailers were broadly grouped and symbolized (green to red) based on the likelihood that someone would be able to readily find fruits/vegetables and other nutritious foods. For example, convenience stores tend to offer fewer nutritious foods (red symbol) compared to farm markets (green symbol). See the Data Guide at the end of the atlas for more information.
dataset.title: Food Retailers Atlas, 2011
